measurement: Gate-3 FILTER-CELLS lever — fresh filter-share ranking on current
  main (post Phases A+B lowbd wiring AND Phase-C i16 transform). Establishes:
  (1) the 2K/4K mosaic gate cells contain NO CDEF / NO LR / NO superres —
  deblock is the ONLY post-recon filter there (run_post_filters == apply_deblock
  inclusive); (2) deblock residual is a stable 1.73-1.77x vs C (+174M/+169M per
  4K decode, 15-17% of each 4K cell's gap), kernel-dominated (516 Ir/call over
  533k calls, scalar tap gathers/scatters = 37.5% of kernel Ir); (3) q32 filter
  ranking is LR/wiener 9.25x (kernel 11.3x vs C avx2), CDEF 4.11x (scalar
  find_dir + u16 filter kernel), deblock 1.68x; the LR delegation widen/narrow
  copies are only 0.25M/dec at 352x288 (delegation-copy hypothesis REFUTED at
  this size — the kernel shape is the gap).
git commit (measured): 1616a1ae (origin/main at capture; jj workspace
  zenav1-aom--g3filters, no code changes at capture).
git commit (landing): the commit this .meta lands in.
date: 2026-07-22/23 UTC (profiles captured ~20:25Z 07-22, analyzed 07-23).
host: dedicated aom-rs workstation (container).
oracle: upstream/ submodule libaom v3.14.1 @ 03087864, Release, SIMD on,
  linked in-process via aom-sys-ref shim_decode_av1_kf.

COMMANDS (exact):
  cargo build --profile profiling -p zenav1-aom-bench --bin gate3_profile
  for cell/iters in dec_352x288_q32/12 dec_mosaic_2k_cq20/3 dec_mosaic_2k_cq40/3 \
      dec_mosaic_4k_cq20/3 dec_mosaic_4k_cq40/3:
    AOM_CONFORMANCE_DIR=/root/aom-rs/conformance/data valgrind --tool=callgrind \
      --callgrind-out-file=/tmp/g3cg/cg_<cell>.out \
      ./target/profiling/gate3_profile dec port <cell> <iters>
  callgrind_annotate --inclusive=yes [--threshold=100] /tmp/g3cg/cg_<cell>.out
  callgrind_annotate --auto=yes --threshold=99   (kernel line attribution)

RATIO METHOD: port = inclusive Ir of aom_decode::frame::decode_frame_obus /
  (iters+1) port decodes; C = inclusive Ir of shim_decode_av1_kf (1 decode,
  includes codec init+destroy, which slightly UNDERSTATES port/C). Ir is
  deterministic and load-independent. Every cell byte-verified in the harness
  setup before profiling.

LANDED FIXES MEASURED IN THIS FILE (same method, same cells):
  fix1 = deblock u8 kernel load/store vectorization (loopfilter/simd.rs;
    horizontal-edge contiguous [u8;4] taps + vertical-edge staged [u8;W] row
    windows; i32x4 math untouched; strided-gather fallback kept).
    4K cq40 −2.85% (2.153x→2.092x), 4K cq20 −1.90% (1.781x→1.747x),
    2K cq40 −3.10% (2.301x→2.229x), q32 −1.17%.
  fix2 = wiener scratch reuse + vector load/store (restore/wiener.rs
    WienerScratch + [u16;8] fixed-array widen/narrow in wiener_impl only;
    scalar twin untouched; scratch threaded via filter_unit/filter_plane +
    pick.rs PlaneCtx). q32 −3.87% on top of fix1 (2.151x→2.067x; LR stage
    −20.7%, kernel −24.7%).
  Gates run per fix: loopfilter_lowbd_diff, lpf_simd_diff, lf_apply_diff,
  lpf_diff, kernels_diff, wiener_simd_diff, frame_walk_diff, pick_search —
  all green; full decode conformance (default + AOM_FORCE_SCALAR=1) run
  before push (see the landing commit).

HONEST LIMITS:
- Ir only; NO wall-clock this pass (a concurrent transform agent makes wall
  noisy; the coordinator runs the final wall measurement).
- Superres cost is NOT measured (no superres stream in the bench cell set);
  its share is unknown, not zero.
- The q32 C LR figure excludes av1_loop_restoration_filter_frame_init (251,485
  Ir); including it the LR ratio is 7.49x instead of 9.25x — still the top
  q32 item either way.
- The C module symbols (av1_loop_filter_frame_mt etc.) are entry-inclusive
  within the C decode subtree; libc leaf attribution differences vs the port
  module rollup are the same caveat as gate3_decode_profile_2026-07-19.md.
